<doc id="1120267" wikidata="Q2039418" url="?curid=1120267" title="Santa Teresa, Espírito Santo">
<text>Santa Teresa is a municipality located in the Brazilian state of Espírito Santo. Its population was 23,724 (2020) and its area is 695 km2.

The municipality contains the Augusto Ruschi Biological Reserve, a fully protected area.

==Notable people==

Augusto Ruschi was a Brazilian agronomist, ecologist, and naturalist. Ruschi was interested in the study of plants and animals since childhood, allowing him to know in depth several branches of biology, becoming a respected specialist in hummingbirds and orchids in Brazil. 

Anderson Varejão of the NBA&#x27;s Cleveland Cavaliers is originally from Santa Teresa.

